00:15:24,383 --> 00:15:25,645
- That thing has a name.

509
00:15:25,689 --> 00:15:26,907
- It's Muffin.

510
00:15:26,951 --> 00:15:28,300
- Well, thanks to Muffin,
we lost Lyndon.

511
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:31,173
- Yes.
But also thanks to Muffin,

512
00:15:31,216 --> 00:15:34,088
I just solved the case
of who killed Pappy Boyle.

513
00:15:34,132 --> 00:15:36,134
- We're right here.

514
00:15:36,178 --> 00:15:38,267
- Yeah. I didn't think
it would feed back.

515
00:15:38,310 --> 00:15:40,704
- Oh, no, Rosa.
They're leaving together.

516
00:15:40,747 --> 00:15:41,661
What are we gonna do?

517
00:15:41,705 --> 00:15:42,880
- We stop them.

518
00:15:42,923 --> 00:15:43,924
Even if it means we have
to kill Todd.

519
00:15:43,968 --> 00:15:46,405
- Smart.
Let's go.

520
00:15:46,449 --> 00:15:47,319
- Looking for someone?

521
00:15:47,363 --> 00:15:49,713
- Sir.
Uh, what's going on?

522
00:15:49,756 --> 00:15:52,281
- What's going on is that you
were trying to manipulate me,

523
00:15:52,324 --> 00:15:54,370
but it is I
who manipulated you.

524
00:15:54,413 --> 00:15:55,501
How does it feel

525
00:15:55,545 --> 00:15:58,417
to suckle from
your own tainted teat?

526
00:15:58,461 --> 00:16:00,114
- Not as bad as it feels
to hear you say "suckle."

527
00:16:00,158 --> 00:16:02,595
- So you were never really
going home with Todd?

528
00:16:02,639 --> 00:16:05,555
- You actually think I would
have relations with him?

529
00:16:05,598 --> 00:16:07,426
His watch has a cloth strap.

530
00:16:07,470 --> 00:16:08,601
- I really thought
we had something.

531
00:16:08,645 --> 00:16:10,429
- Wake up, Todd.
I'm out of your league.

532
00:16:10,473 --> 00:16:12,910
You thought you could meddle
in my personal life,

533
00:16:12,953 --> 00:16:15,782
but I was ten moves ahead
the whole time.

534
00:16:15,826 --> 00:16:16,957
And now, checkmate.

535
00:16:17,001 --> 00:16:18,176
- Ooh.
I love chess.

536
00:16:18,220 --> 00:16:19,438
Have you seen
"The Queen's Gambit"?

537
00:16:19,482 --> 00:16:21,832
It's a TV show.
- Todd, I swear to God.

538
00:16:21,875 --> 00:16:24,530
- The person who killed Pappy
wasn't a person at all.

539
00:16:24,574 --> 00:16:25,792
It was Muffin.

540
00:16:25,836 --> 00:16:27,185
- I checked her mouth,

541
00:16:27,229 --> 00:16:29,274
and Muffin had the same ulcers
that Pappy had.

542
00:16:29,318 --> 00:16:31,624
Muffin ate the poison,
and then Pappy drank her milk.

543
00:16:31,668 --> 00:16:33,539
- Charles, you said nutria
could open doors.

544
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:35,585
Muffin must've let herself
into the barn.

545
00:16:35,628 --> 00:16:37,195
- Which explains why we found
her hair on the box.

546
00:16:37,239 --> 00:16:38,979
- So Lyndon was innocent.

547
00:16:39,023 --> 00:16:40,807
- Wait, how did you know
it was Muffin's hair?

548
00:16:40,851 --> 00:16:42,287
Did you get
the DNA report back?

549
00:16:42,331 --> 00:16:43,506
- Exactly.
- Wait, but I thought

550
00:16:43,549 --> 00:16:44,855
the report was gonna
take a week

551
00:16:44,898 --> 00:16:46,030
because of
the lab tech's allergies.

552
00:16:46,073 --> 00:16:47,336
- Uh-huh, uh-huh, uh-huh.

553
00:16:47,379 --> 00:16:49,120
But then they decided
to use a subcontractor

554
00:16:49,163 --> 00:16:50,600
who was allergy-free,
so let's just move on

555
00:16:50,643 --> 00:16:51,862
and talk about
something else immediately.

556
00:16:51,905 --> 00:16:53,037
Three "uh-huh's"?

557
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,908
Clearly you're lying
about something.

558
00:16:54,952 --> 00:16:56,040
- Why you being a jerk to me?

559
00:16:56,083 --> 00:16:57,346
- Show me the report, Jake.

560
00:16:57,389 --> 00:16:59,086
- Okay, fine.
But just look at the top result

561
00:16:59,130 --> 00:17:01,306
'cause that's all
that matters.

562
00:17:01,350 --> 00:17:03,047
"Specimen hair was rodent
in nature."

563
00:17:03,090 --> 00:17:04,701
and that's that.

564
00:17:04,744 --> 00:17:07,878
- Oh, my God.

565
00:17:07,921 --> 00:17:09,401
I'm not a Boyle.

566
00:17:11,969 --> 00:17:14,101
- Okay.
I love you too, Dad.

567
00:17:14,145 --> 00:17:15,277
Did you guys change clothes?

568
00:17:15,320 --> 00:17:16,974
- Yeah, Charles.
It's tomorrow now.

569
00:17:17,017 --> 00:17:18,715
You been on the phone
for 14 hours.

570
00:17:18,758 --> 00:17:20,412
- Well, you know
what they say,

571
00:17:20,456 --> 00:17:22,632
"Time flies when God
pulls down his pants

572
00:17:22,675 --> 00:17:24,460
and takes a dump
on your life."

573
00:17:24,503 --> 00:17:26,113
- Oh, buddy.
I'm so sorry.

574
00:17:26,157 --> 00:17:28,638
- Being a Boyle was
the backbone of my identity.

575
00:17:28,681 --> 00:17:31,467
Without the Boyle backbone,
I'm just a bag of flesh.

576
00:17:31,510 --> 00:17:33,425
I'm goo.
- Come on, you're not goo.

577
00:17:33,469 --> 00:17:35,079
Being a Boyle is about more
than blood.

578
00:17:35,122 --> 00:17:36,254
It's what's in your heart.

579
00:17:36,298 --> 00:17:37,690
- Blood is what's in
your heart.

580
00:17:37,734 --> 00:17:38,996
You're making it worse, Jake.

581
00:17:39,039 --> 00:17:40,476
- Okay, fine.
Then what about Nikolaj?

582
00:17:40,519 --> 00:17:41,825
He was adopted, so technically,

583
00:17:41,868 --> 00:17:43,435
he's not a Boyle,
but that never bothered you.

584
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:44,828
- I didn't even think
about Niko.

585
00:17:44,871 --> 00:17:47,091
He was already a Boyle
once removed

586
00:17:47,134 --> 00:17:49,311
which is tough enough.
Now he's twice removed?

587
00:17:49,354 --> 00:17:51,965
Twice-removed Boyles
are a total clown show,

588
00:17:52,009 --> 00:17:55,447
okay?
Niko's basically Cousin Andrea.

589
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:57,362
Sorry, Andrea.

590
00:17:57,406 --> 00:17:59,799
- I know what I am.

591
00:17:59,843 --> 00:18:01,497
- Well, damn.
- Look, let's go home.

592
00:18:01,540 --> 00:18:03,368
- We're leaving?
What about the funeral?

593
00:18:03,412 --> 00:18:04,500
What about the eulogy?

594
00:18:04,543 --> 00:18:05,805
- I don't feel right
giving it now.

595
00:18:05,849 --> 00:18:08,242
Sam offered to step in.
I'll have him do it.

596
00:18:08,286 --> 00:18:09,722
- No, no, no.
Wait.

597
00:18:09,766 --> 00:18:11,028
Assemble the cousins.

598
00:18:11,071 --> 00:18:12,986
Today, we learned
that Pappy Boyle's death

599
00:18:13,030 --> 00:18:14,118
was not foul play.

600
00:18:14,161 --> 00:18:16,120
But even though
there was no murder,

601
00:18:16,163 --> 00:18:17,469
there was a robbery.

602
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:20,124
Charles had his sense
of self stolen from him

603
00:18:20,167 --> 00:18:21,430
by Sam Boyle.

604
00:18:21,473 --> 00:18:23,083
You said it yourself, Charles,

605
00:18:23,127 --> 00:18:25,390
the Boyles have a long history
of cousin-on-cousin jealousy.

606
00:18:25,434 --> 00:18:28,088
Sam couldn't stand that you
were chosen to give the eulogy.

607
00:18:28,132 --> 00:18:29,699
Think about it.

608
00:18:29,742 --> 00:18:31,222
It was Sam who made sure we
knew the will was missing.

609
00:18:31,265 --> 00:18:33,529
- We can't find Pappy's will.

610
00:18:33,572 --> 00:18:36,706
- Then Sam again who suggested
you all get your DNA tested.

611
00:18:36,749 --> 00:18:39,012
- Why not take a hair
from every Boyle?

612
00:18:39,056 --> 00:18:41,841
- And finally, Sam who made
sure we all knew the results.

613
00:18:41,885 --> 00:18:43,843
- Did you get
the DNA report back?

614
00:18:43,887 --> 00:18:46,150
This is ridiculous.
I love Charles.

615
00:18:46,193 --> 00:18:47,543
- Okay, well then.

616
00:18:47,586 --> 00:18:48,805
I'm sure you wouldn't mind
giving him a hug then.

617
00:18:48,848 --> 00:18:50,067
Since you love him so much.

618
00:18:50,110 --> 00:18:53,331
- Sure.
I always like to hug my cousin.

619
00:18:53,375 --> 00:18:54,898
- He's gushing!

620
00:18:54,941 --> 00:18:55,812
- Darn it.

621
00:18:55,855 --> 00:18:57,509
I thought these would hide it,

622
00:18:57,553 --> 00:18:59,903
but I gushed
through my pit diapers.

623
00:18:59,946 --> 00:19:01,295
All right, fine.

624
00:19:01,339 --> 00:19:03,602
I always suspected
that Charles wasn't one of us.

625
00:19:03,646 --> 00:19:05,648
I mean, he went
through puberty at 13,

626
00:19:05,691 --> 00:19:07,258
instead of 25,

627
00:19:07,301 --> 00:19:09,086
like a normal Boyle.

628
00:19:09,129 --> 00:19:12,263
And when he got chosen
to give the eulogy,

629
00:19:12,306 --> 00:19:14,091
something inside
of me snapped.

630
00:19:14,134 --> 00:19:15,440
So I hid the will.

631
00:19:15,484 --> 00:19:16,702
I admit it.

632
00:19:16,746 --> 00:19:17,747
Are you happy now?

633
00:19:17,790 --> 00:19:19,009
- Very.
- Not at all.

634
00:19:19,052 --> 00:19:20,880
- Wait, what?
Charles, we solved the case.

635
00:19:20,924 --> 00:19:23,056
He confessed.
- Doesn't matter.

636
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:24,754
I'm still not a Boyle.

637
00:19:24,797 --> 00:19:28,453
I'm just a normal person.

638
00:19:28,497 --> 00:19:30,803
Normal from snout to anus.

639
00:19:34,416 --> 00:19:35,765
- We wanted to apologize.

640
00:19:35,808 --> 00:19:38,550
- And if you wanna gloat
about how you outsmarted us,

641
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:40,030
go ahead.
We deserve it.

642
00:19:40,073 --> 00:19:41,814
- I won't be doing
any gloating.

643
00:19:41,858 --> 00:19:43,816
I mean, I did last night.
I went home and had a drink

644
00:19:43,860 --> 00:19:46,123
to toast to your humiliation.

645
00:19:46,166 --> 00:19:47,211
But it didn't feel right,

646
00:19:47,254 --> 00:19:48,386
because I had no one
to toast with,

647
00:19:48,430 --> 00:19:49,779
no one to share my glee.

648
00:19:49,822 --> 00:19:54,174
I had won,
but I was alone.

649
00:19:54,218 --> 00:19:55,959
And I realized,

650
00:19:56,002 --> 00:19:58,657
this is exactly what
I'm doing to Kevin.

651
00:19:58,701 --> 00:20:01,051
Trying to win therapy.

652
00:20:01,094 --> 00:20:02,487
And it hit me.

653
00:20:02,531 --> 00:20:06,491
I care so much about winning

654
00:20:06,535 --> 00:20:09,886
that I've lost everything.

655
00:20:09,929 --> 00:20:11,975
- Tell Kevin how you feel.

656
00:20:12,018 --> 00:20:14,630
- It's raining.
You could run to him.

657
00:20:14,673 --> 00:20:16,109
- This is the real world,
Santiago.

658
00:20:16,153 --> 00:20:20,113
Relationships end
in unsatisfying ways every day.

659
00:20:20,157 --> 00:20:22,115
People don't run
to each other in the rain.

660
00:20:22,159 --> 00:20:24,509
- Raymond!
Raymond Holt!

661
00:20:24,553 --> 00:20:26,598
- Kevin?

662
00:20:28,470 --> 00:20:30,123
- Raymond!

663
00:20:35,564 --> 00:20:37,304
Raymond, am I too late?

664
00:20:37,348 --> 00:20:38,654
- Too late?

665
00:20:38,697 --> 00:20:40,090
- My friend saw
your dating profile

666
00:20:40,133 --> 00:20:42,266
and your photo
without collar stays.

667
00:20:42,309 --> 00:20:44,529
I thought I'd lost you.

668
00:20:44,573 --> 00:20:47,576
- You will never lose me.

669
00:20:47,619 --> 00:20:49,012
I'll do anything
to keep you.

670
00:20:49,055 --> 00:20:51,231
I'll compromise on everything.
The work, the—

671
00:20:54,452 --> 00:21:01,546
♪

672
00:21:02,591 --> 00:21:05,768
- Nancy Meyers never fails.

673
00:21:05,811 --> 00:21:08,118
- Now that we're doing it,
it feels kinda weird

674
00:21:08,161 --> 00:21:09,859
to be staring at your friends
while they kiss.

675
00:21:09,902 --> 00:21:12,601
- Are you kidding?
It's beautiful.

676
00:21:12,644 --> 00:21:14,603
♪

677
00:21:14,646 --> 00:21:19,085
- I love you.

678
00:21:19,129 --> 00:21:22,262
- Okay, I'm packed.
Let's go home.

679
00:21:22,306 --> 00:21:23,612
- Charles, I'm sorry.

680
00:21:23,655 --> 00:21:25,004
I feel like
this was all my fault.

681
00:21:25,048 --> 00:21:26,571
- Why?
Did you inseminate my mother?

682
00:21:26,615 --> 00:21:27,833
- What?
Ew, no.

683
00:21:27,877 --> 00:21:30,009
- Don't say ew.
She's my one blood relation.

684
00:21:30,053 --> 00:21:32,446
Remember, I'm not
a real Boyle.

685
00:21:32,490 --> 00:21:33,970
- Okay, fine.

686
00:21:34,013 --> 00:21:35,232
Maybe you're not
a real Boyle.

687
00:21:35,275 --> 00:21:36,276
But what if

688
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:37,277
you're a true Boyle?

689
00:21:37,321 --> 00:21:38,714
What if

690
00:21:38,757 --> 00:21:40,106
you're The One True Boyle?

691
00:21:40,150 --> 00:21:41,368
- No, no.
You want me to open

692
00:21:41,412 --> 00:21:42,369
the Grandmother Dough.

693
00:21:42,413 --> 00:21:43,545
That jar is stuck shut.

694
00:21:43,588 --> 00:21:45,198
Nobody's ever been able
to do it.

695
00:21:45,242 --> 00:21:46,591
- But you have to try.

696
00:21:46,635 --> 00:21:48,811
Terry, go grab it.

697
00:21:48,854 --> 00:21:52,118
All right, now let's reassemble
those cousins.

698
00:21:53,293 --> 00:21:54,904
- I'm not gonna
be able to do this,

699
00:21:54,947 --> 00:21:56,732
and I'm gonna be
even more humiliated.

700
00:21:56,775 --> 00:21:58,995
- Just try.
I believe in you.

701
00:22:00,866 --> 00:22:02,651
So did you loosen it?

702
00:22:02,694 --> 00:22:03,956
- I tried, but it's slippery,

703
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:04,914
and that thing
is sealed on tight.

704
00:22:04,957 --> 00:22:06,393
I couldn't budge it.

705
00:22:06,437 --> 00:22:08,787
- Oh, no.
Uh, hey, Charles.

706
00:22:08,831 --> 00:22:10,441
Remember when I said
that I believed in you?

707
00:22:10,484 --> 00:22:11,660
- Yes.

708
00:22:11,703 --> 00:22:12,617
It's the entire reason
I'm doing this.

709
00:22:12,661 --> 00:22:14,532
- Oh.
Godspeed.

710
00:22:21,321 --> 00:22:28,198
♪

711
00:22:29,068 --> 00:22:30,200
- Ah!

712
00:22:30,243 --> 00:22:31,070
I did it!

713
00:22:31,114 --> 00:22:32,637
- He's The One True Boyle.

714
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:37,511
- Oh, my God.
What is that stench?

715
00:22:37,555 --> 00:22:38,817
It's the Grandmother Dough.

716
00:22:38,861 --> 00:22:39,949
- It smells horrible.

717
00:22:39,992 --> 00:22:42,647
- Not to a Boyle.

718
00:22:42,691 --> 00:22:45,955
Pappy's hugs were long
and firm.

719
00:22:45,998 --> 00:22:47,304
- Okay, here's what I think
might've happened.

720
00:22:47,347 --> 00:22:49,436
You loosened the jar,
but you didn't realize it

721
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:50,568
because you're a Godzilla man,

722
00:22:50,612 --> 00:22:52,091
and you don't know
your own strength.

723
00:22:52,135 --> 00:22:53,789
- First of all, thank you
for calling me a Godzilla man.

724
00:22:53,832 --> 00:22:55,268
- Yeah.
- Secondly, that's not it.

725
00:22:55,312 --> 00:22:56,922
The jar was too slippery.
- All right, how about this?

726
00:22:56,966 --> 00:22:58,707
Charles was so freaked out
about not being a Boyle

727
00:22:58,750 --> 00:23:01,231
that he got an adrenaline rush,
and that made him stronger.

728
00:23:01,274 --> 00:23:03,189
- Or maybe Charles
is the One True Boyle.

729
00:23:03,233 --> 00:23:05,452
- And I know that Pappy's
up there

730
00:23:05,496 --> 00:23:07,672
shopping for beige slacks

731
00:23:07,716 --> 00:23:10,936
at that Mervyn's in the sky.

732
00:23:10,980 --> 00:23:13,635
Ah, Mervyn's!

733
00:23:13,678 --> 00:23:15,158
- Yeah, he's
the One True Boyle.

734
00:23:15,201 --> 00:23:17,334
- Not a doctor.
Shh.

735
00:23:17,377 --> 00:23:18,814
- Fremulon.

